# Tea Estate Backend Requirements

This frontend is a **UI prototype with no API integration**. All data lives in React Context (`app/dashboard/context.tsx`) with hardcoded seed data. There are no `fetch`/`axios` calls, no env vars, and no route protection.

Your Express.js backend should be built from the **TypeScript interfaces and UI behavior** in the components. Below is a full specification.

---

## 1. What the app does

**Tea Estate Management System** for Sri Lankan tea plantations:

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| Login | Email/password sign-in |
| Dashboard | KPIs, charts, expense breakdown, harvest by section |
| Estates | Estates + nested sections |
| Users | Admin / Planter / Supervisor accounts |
| Employees | Field workers with service skills |
| Services | Work types with rates (LKR) |
| Daily Assignments | Daily work + worker units + payroll |
| Expenses | Estate expenses with approval workflow |
| Reminders | Calendar events |
| Reports | Assignments, payments, expenses, harvest + CSV export |
| Profile | Edit profile + change password |
| Backups | Manual/auto DB export |
| TV Dashboard | Full-screen live estate display |

**Currency:** LKR (`en-LK` formatting)  
**Locale context:** Sri Lanka (NIC numbers, estates in Nuwara Eliya, Badulla, Kandy)

