## 8. Frontend gaps to account for

These affect backend design decisions:

| Gap | Backend implication |
|-----|---------------------|
| No API layer | You define the contract; frontend will need integration later |
| Login email mismatch | `admin@gmail.com` vs seed `admin@greenleaf.com` â€” pick one seed user |
| Profile â‰  User table | Merge into one `User` model with `address` field |
| `planter`/`supervisor` are strings | Keep as text or add optional FK to `User` |
| Employee categories use service **names** | Prefer FK join table; return names in API |
| No assignment approve UI | Expose `PATCH /assignments/:id/status` anyway |
| `KG` missing from service form | Support in API enum |
| Hardcoded demo dates | Use real server dates in analytics |
| No password on User CRUD | Add password on user create + reset flow |
| Duplicate `UserProfile` type | Single source in API response |

